a. List the contents of dir1 and all its descendants:

bash

ls -R dir1



b. List the contents of dir3:
i. Alphabetical Order:

bash

ls -l dir3 | sort

ii. Sorted on Time of modification, newest first:

bash

ls -lt dir3

iii. Sorted on Size:

bash

ls -lS dir3

iv. Reverse of all above:

bash

ls -lR --sort=none dir3 | sort -r

v. Long listing of files Sorted on Size with smallest first and size displayed in human-readable form:

bash

ls -lhS dir3
